cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) - The paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques to obtain accurate 3D models of the teeth and to track the motion of the jaw. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) - The paper discusses the use of the jaw kinematic model in computer graphics applications, such as animation. 
3. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the development of an intuitive interface for animators to explore realistic jaw motions. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a modification of autoencoder neural networks known as Nonlinear PCA to capture the nonlinear trajectories of the moving mandible. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the modeling of human facial anatomy, which is often used in multimedia applications such as virtual reality and video games.
